{{Distinguish|Template:Em dash}}
{{documentation subpage}}
<!--Categories where indicated at the bottom of this page, please; interwikis at Wikidata (see [[Wikipedia:Wikidata]])-->
{{Short description|Template to output an n-dash character}}
{{High-use}}
{{COinS safe}}
{{Template shortcuts|ndash|endash|nsndns}}
This template produces an '''[[en dash]]''' (–), which is longer than a [[hyphen]] (-) but shorter than an [[em dash]] (—).

==Usage==
The primary uses of an en dash are:

* To indicate a range of numbers or dates (e.g. {{xt|1914{{en dash}}1918}})
* To show a relationship between things (e.g. {{xt|a New York{{en dash}}London flight}})

For further detail on dash usage, see [[MOS:DASH]].

==TemplateData==
{{Format TemplateData|JSON={"params":{},"description":
"This template produces an [[en dash]] (–) character. It has the same effect as the HTML escape sequence <code>&amp;ndash;</code>."
} }}
Syntax:<code><nowiki>{{en dash}}</nowiki></code>

== See also ==
* {{tl|Non breaking en dash}}
* {{tl|Spaced en dash space}}
* {{tl|Spaced en dash}}
* {{tl|Em dash}}

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
<!-- Categories below this line; interwikis at Wikidata -->

[[Category:Typing-aid templates]]
}}</includeonly>

